entries.title: Russian train collected weapons from North Korea for Russian mercenaries, US says
entries.description: The US says North Korea will continue supplying weapons to Wagner Group mercenaries in Ukraine - as it released an image it said showed a shipment of rockets and missiles being collected.

entries.title: West fails to make decision on sending tanks to Ukraine
entries.description: Western nations have failed to agree on a deal to send much-wanted Leopard 2 tanks to Ukraine, despite holding a summit in Germany.

entries.title: Education minister set to replace Jacinda Ardern as New Zealand prime minister
entries.description: The New Zealand education minister is set to become the country's next prime minister after Jacinda Ardern resigned from the role.

entries.title: Friction behind the smiles at defence chiefs meeting - as Ukraine tank saga rolls on
entries.description: There was a sense of friction behind the unified smiles and handshakes at a meeting of allies to pledge more weapons for Ukraine.

entries.title: 'Polar Preet' sets new record for female solo polar expedition
entries.description: An Army officer known as "Polar Preet" has broken the world record for the longest, solo, unaided polar expedition by a woman.

entries.title: Climate crisis 'sliding down agenda', warns global energy watchdog
entries.description: Climate change is slipping down the international agenda, raising the risk governments will slow their pace in reducing greenhouse gas emissions, the head of a global energy watchdog has told Sky News.

entries.title: 'This is such a stupid tank': Ukrainian commander's plea for Western upgrades
entries.description: A Soviet-era T-72 rumbles through woodland belching thick black smoke as it fishtails over the frozen mud near the battered Ukrainian city of Bakhmut.

entries.title: How faster, deadlier tanks could turn the tide in Ukraine
entries.description: Why all this talk all of a sudden about tanks?

entries.title: Andrew Tate to be detained for another 30 days over allegations of sexual assault and exploitation
entries.description: Andrew Tate and his brother Tristan will stay in custody until 27 February after a Romanian court extended their police detention.

entries.title: Dani Alves arrested in Spain over alleged nightclub sexual assault
entries.description: Ex-Barcelona defender Dani Alves has been arrested on suspicion of sexual assault after allegedly touching a woman under her clothes at a nightclub without her consent.

entries.title: Rocks thrown as thousands of protesters march in Peru calling for president to step down
entries.description: Thousands of protesters descended on Peru's capital and clashed with police as they demanded President Dina Boluarte leave office.

entries.title: Indian wrestlers accuse sports body chief of sexual harassment
entries.description: Olympic medal-winning Indian wrestlers have accused the chief of their sport's governing body and its coaches of sexually harassing female athletes.

entries.title: Wagner Group suffers heavy losses in Ukraine as their boss steps into the spotlight
entries.description: The graves are all fresh. Row after row of them, almost identical. The same mound of sandy soil, the same black, red and yellow wreath mounted with a golden star.

entries.title: Scandal-ridden George Santos denies performing at drag show in Brazil
entries.description: Scandal-ridden US politician George Santos has denied participating in a drag show after video appeared to show him in a dress, necklace and earrings at a gay pride parade in Brazil.

entries.title: Greta Thunberg accuses Davos elite of putting 'corporate greed' above people and planet
entries.description: Greta Thunberg has accused the political and business elite at the World Economic Forum in Davos of putting "corporate greed" and "short-term profits" above the planet.

entries.title: 'I slept well for first time in a long time': Jacinda Ardern speaks of 'relief' after announcing she will step down as PM
entries.description: Jacinda Ardern said she "slept well for the first time in a long" after announcing she was stepping down as prime minister.

entries.title: 'Toadzilla': Giant cane toad found weighing 2.7kg
entries.description: A giant cane toad dubbed "Toadzilla" has been discovered in Australia.

entries.title: Alec Baldwin charges are a sign that a criminal reckoning awaits him - but he remains defiant and even bullish
entries.description: It has been 15 months since cinematographer Halyna Hutchins was shot dead during rehearsals on set in New Mexico.

entries.title: A new Russian offensive appears to be imminent - that's why Ukraine says it needs as many tanks as possible
entries.description: This is the most significant American package of weaponry to Ukraine since the Russians invaded.

entries.title: Ardern may be dodging humiliation by quitting now - but she's sure of a lasting place as a star | Adam Boulton
entries.description: At a time when ageing rockstars are embarking on seemingly endless farewell tours, and the US is contemplating a presidential election between two octogenarian men, the world's most famous female political superstar will be out of office and out of parliament before her 43rd birthday in July.
